Constant.text: In this Vizzy program you will find a lot of "fUNk" blocks. These take a text input in a language called Funky Trees.
This language combines a series of game inputs and mathematical operators and functions, being super powerful.
You can find more info and the documentation for Funky Trees in https://wnp78.github.io/JunoXml/InputController.html
The values calculated with "fUNk" are then put into variables, and these are then referenced directly in the inputs of some parts, to use those values as inputs
You will also come across frequent references to "PID," indicating the use of PID controller.
For more details on PID controllers, visit: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proportional%E2%80%93integral%E2%80%93derivative_controller
Calculate The Rotation Angle of Upper & Lower Shaft
Calculate the real AGL using Ray Cast

Helicopter Mode / Fixed Wing Mode:
Pitch: Elevation / Pitch Rate
Roll: Lateral / Roll Rate
Yaw: Yaw
Throttle/Brake: Forwards Velocity / Pusher Prop
Cascade PID Controller: Commanded Velocity > Commanded Pitch/Roll Angle > Commanded Angular Velocity

clamp(PID(clamp(0.85 * PID(clamp(15 * PID(clamp(smooth(Throttle, 0.5) - Brake, -0.25, 1) * 40, dot(FD.SurfaceVelocity, FD.CraftForward) * cos(0.0174533 * abs(FD.Pitch)), 0.15, 0, 0), -clamp(50 * atan((Ray_Altitude - 0.4) / 5), 0, 45), clamp(50 * atan((Ray_Altitude - 0.4) / 5), 0, 15)), -FD.Pitch, 0.045, 0, 0), -0.85, 0.85), -x(FD.AngularVelocity), 10, 0.3, 0.02), -1, 1)

clamp(PID(clamp(1.2 * PID(clamp(25 * PID(Roll * 15, dot(FD.SurfaceVelocity, FD.CraftRight) * cos(0.0174533 * abs(FD.BankAngle)), 0.1, 0, 0), -25, 25), FD.BankAngle, 0.03, 0, 0), -1.2, 1.2), z(FD.AngularVelocity), 1.25, 0.3, 0.01), -1, 1)

clamp(PID(-smooth(Pitch - smooth(Throttle, 0.2) * clamp01(1 - Ray_Altitude / 5), 0.5) * 4 + 1 * clamp(PID(Target_ASL,FD.AltitudeAboveSeaLevel, 1, 0.01, 0), -1, 1),FD.VerticalSurfaceVelocity, 0.425, 0.1, 0) / cos(FD.Pitch * 0.0174533) / cos(FD.BankAngle * 0.0174533), -1, 1)
